<sec>
<st>
Biography</st>
<p>

Born in what is today <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../457/3457.xml">
Belarus</link></country>
 in 1866, Berligne was an activist in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../593/1031593.xml">
Hovevei Zion</link> and attended the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../785/8234785.xml">
First Zionist Congress</link>. An opponent of the <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_district wordnetid="108491826" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.8">
<country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../790/1188790.xml">
British Uganda Program</link></country>
</district>
</location>
</administrative_district>
</region>
, he visited <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../278/22278.xml">
Ottoman</link></country>
 <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<region wordnetid="108630039" confidence="0.8">
<center wordnetid="108523483" confidence="0.8">
<area wordnetid="108497294" confidence="0.8">
<see wordnetid="108586825" confidence="0.8">
<seat wordnetid="108647945" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../732/1114732.xml">
Palestine</link></district>
</location>
</seat>
</see>
</area>
</center>
</region>
</region>
 in 1905, and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../513/351513.xml">
immigrated</link> two years later, settling in <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<vicinity wordnetid="108641113" confidence="0.8">
<area wordnetid="108497294" confidence="0.8">
<village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<settlement wordnetid="108672562" confidence="0.8">
<geographical_area wordnetid="108574314" confidence="0.8">
<section wordnetid="108648322" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../035/608035.xml">
Jaffa</link></section>
</geographical_area>
</settlement>
</location>
</village>
</area>
</vicinity>
</region>
. After arriving, he founded an olive oil and soap factory in the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../606/55606.xml">
Haifa</link> and <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.8">
<region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<region wordnetid="108630039" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<tract wordnetid="108673395" confidence="0.8">
<geographical_area wordnetid="108574314" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../562/313562.xml">
Gush Dan</link></geographical_area>
</tract>
</location>
</region>
</region>
</site>
 area, with the principle of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../285/16338285.xml">
Hebrew Labour</link>.</p>
<p>

A founder of the <party wordnetid="108256968" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../716/7951716.xml">
Progressive Party</link></party>
, Berligne later joined the <party wordnetid="108256968" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../636/1353636.xml">
General Zionists</link></party>
 and was a member of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../643/2524643.xml">
Vaad Leumi</link>. He served as treasurer of the Vaad between 1920 and 1948, as well as manager of <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../973/735973.xml">
Bank Hapoalim</link></company>
.</p>
